{
    "title": "Almost Happened",
    "level": "C1",
    "pattern": {
        "title": "Nearly: meinata, olla vähällä",
        "summary": "'Meinata' does double duty in speech: mä meinasin unohtaa = I almost forgot, and mitä sä meinaat tehä = what do you plan to do. 'Olla vähällä' + verb also means nearly: oltiin vähäl myöhästyy. And when disaster just missed you: Vähält piti!",
        "examples": [
            "Mä meinasin unohtaa koko jutun. = I almost forgot the whole thing.",
            "Vähält piti! = That was close!",
            "Mitä sä meinaat tehä ens kesänä? = What are you planning to do next summer?"
        ]
    },
    "sentences": [
